This paper is about neural network compression, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with techniques for making neural networks more efficient. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper evaluates the compression techniques on models trained on ImageNet, which is a popular dataset for computer vision tasks. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as neural network compression is a sub-field of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with techniques for optimizing neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses different ways of structuring neural networks to make them more efficient.
